  <h1>Claude Code Integration</h1>
  <p class="lead">Live status lights so you know which agents are thinking and which are waiting. I boiled several oceans to make these little dots change color.</p>

  <h2>What you get</h2>
  <p>When Claude Code is running in an Ouijit terminal, the terminal card shows a live status indicator: thinking or idle. That's it. It's a colored dot. You'd be surprised how useful it is when you have 5+ agents running(?) at once.</p>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>Ouijit installs a thin wrapper that shadows the <code>claude</code> command inside its terminals. When you launch Claude Code, the wrapper automatically injects hook settings that report status back to Ouijit. No configuration needed on your end. Just type <code>claude</code> and it's wired up.</p>

  <h2>Notifications</h2>
  <p>When an agent finishes, you'll hear a sound. If the window isn't focused, you also get an OS notification. Alt-tab guilt-free while Claude does the work.</p>

  <h2>What about other agents?</h2>
  <p>Ouijit's terminals work with any CLI agent: Cursor, Aider, Codex, whatever. They just won't get the fancy status lights. Yet. I play favorites for now.</p>
  <p>If your favorite agent has a hook or plugin system, <a href="https://github.com/ouijit/ouijit/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open an issue</a> and I'll see what I can do.</p>

